New Records: Spencer Schwellenbach and Simeon Woods-Richardson had the longest-named starting pitcher matchup in baseball history
Spencer Schwellenbach pitched 4.2 innings without allowing any runs, while Simeon Woods-Richardson lasted 4.2 innings and gave up four earned runs
Key Match Events: The game went into extra innings with the Atlanta Braves winning 8-6
The Braves moved to 72-60 with the win, while the Twins dropped to 72-60 as well
Pre-Game Insights: The Braves' Chris Sale is set to pitch against the Twins' David Festa in the next game
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game had historical significance due to the unique names of the starting pitchers
The Braves are dealing with the absence of Spencer Strider for the rest of the season due to Tommy John surgery
